// The INSTALLED-mods catalog: every mod the build ships, in LOAD order (base
// first, so mods overlay it). This is the wasm-safe index the loader loads -
// never a directory scan. A THIN pointer list: each entry is id (enable key +
// overlay namespace), bundle (the mod's `*.bundle.ron`, asset-root-relative),
// base (true = the base game: enabled by default, locked on in the UI), hidden
// (true = dev/tooling mod: kept out of the player-facing mods list, but still
// installed and enableable by id - examples do so via EnabledMods). The mod's
// METADATA (name, description, author, version...) lives in its own bundle's
// `meta` block; which entries are ENABLED is a runtime concern (EnabledMods,
// persisted separately).
(mods: [
    (
        id: "base",
        bundle: "base/base.bundle.ron",
        base: true,
    ),
    (
        id: "example",
        bundle: "mods/example/example.bundle.ron",
    ),
    (
        id: "craft_cargob",
        bundle: "mods/craft_cargob/craft_cargob.bundle.ron",
    ),
])
